00:17:04.750 --> 00:17:13.310
where people started thinking
about interactive tools.

00:17:13.310 --> 00:17:15.599
I think that was a
big change there.

00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:17.640
NOAH LEVIN: So I want to
shift gears a little bit

00:17:17.640 --> 00:17:19.859
and talk a little bit
about the actual creation

00:17:19.859 --> 00:17:23.099
experience, the experience of
opening up one of these tools

00:17:23.099 --> 00:17:25.430
and creating something,
and how the difference

00:17:25.430 --> 00:17:27.020
between these tools
might actually

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:29.102
affect the outcome of
what you're producing.

00:17:29.102 --> 00:17:31.310
They're very different, if
you've used each of these.

00:17:31.310 --> 00:17:32.518
Some of them are more visual.

00:17:32.518 --> 00:17:34.100
Some of them are code-based.

00:17:34.100 --> 00:17:37.320
They have a different approach
to how you might do it.

00:17:37.320 --> 00:17:39.210
So to start, there's no
one on the panel that

00:17:39.210 --> 00:17:42.190
really works on a
timeline-based tool.

00:17:42.190 --> 00:17:45.910
No one here really-- something
