00:17:45.910 --> 00:17:48.950
Why don't we think-- is
there a reason for that?

00:17:48.950 --> 00:17:50.640
Why don't we have
timeline-based tools

00:17:50.640 --> 00:17:53.359
versus something more free-form?

00:17:53.359 --> 00:17:55.650
KOEN BOK: Well, if you're
building an interactive tool,

00:17:55.650 --> 00:17:57.420
then time is not a constant.

00:17:57.420 --> 00:18:00.220
Stuff like state is
shifting throughout time,

00:18:00.220 --> 00:18:03.192
and it's going to go
through different states

00:18:03.192 --> 00:18:05.150
every time you use the
app and stuff like that.

00:18:05.150 --> 00:18:07.590
So a timeline isn't
very efficient,

00:18:07.590 --> 00:18:10.540
if you're trying to build
these longer interactions.

00:18:10.540 --> 00:18:12.660
Maybe just a show
of a small thing,

00:18:12.660 --> 00:18:15.280
and I think that's the most
obvious reason that that

00:18:15.280 --> 00:18:18.009
wouldn't be the best model
to pick for these new tools.

00:18:18.009 --> 00:18:19.550
NOAH LEVIN: But why
do we think that?

00:18:19.550 --> 00:18:22.490
Even with that being the case,
a lot of people-- at least

00:18:22.490 --> 00:18:25.127
in my experience, and
even seeing at Google--

00:18:25.127 --> 00:18:27.210
are gravitating still to
the timeline-based tools.

00:18:27.210 --> 00:18:29.970
What is it about them that
are making people use them?

00:18:29.970 --> 00:18:32.040
KOEN BOK: Well, I
mean a lot of people

00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:33.600
build a knowledge
around these tools,

00:18:33.600 --> 00:18:36.580
and I think they do
particular things very well.

00:18:36.580 --> 00:18:38.110
And they're still very valuable.

00:18:38.110 --> 00:18:41.660
It's not that we're going
to move After Effects

00:18:41.660 --> 00:18:43.890
out of the market with
our interactive tools.

00:18:43.890 --> 00:18:46.090
I think they're going to
live next to each other,

00:18:46.090 --> 00:18:49.430
and we'll slowly start
taking more of the stuff

00:18:49.430 --> 00:18:51.870
that they're really good at
and taking that into our apps,

00:18:51.870 --> 00:18:52.572
I think.

00:18:52.572 --> 00:18:54.030
PAUL COLTON: One
thing I'll add is,

00:18:54.030 --> 00:18:56.860
time, at least for
interaction, implies

00:18:56.860 --> 00:18:59.760
you know the exact flow that
your user's going to take.

00:18:59.760 --> 00:19:00.270
Right?

00:19:00.270 --> 00:19:03.090
Interaction by definition
means it's random,

00:19:03.090 --> 00:19:05.685
and I think that's fundamentally
why timeline doesn't work.

00:19:05.685 --> 00:19:08.740
And you can imagine, we've
been asked countless times,

00:19:08.740 --> 00:19:10.070
put a timeline in there.

00:19:10.070 --> 00:19:12.940
