00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:40.380
your UIs might change over time?

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:43.040
BRANDON WALKIN: Yeah,
so it's worth noting,

00:20:43.040 --> 00:20:45.730
Origami looks the way
it does, because it's

00:20:45.730 --> 00:20:48.120
an extension on Quartz Composer.

00:20:48.120 --> 00:20:50.610
I wasn't given a team
of engineers and people

00:20:50.610 --> 00:20:53.090
to go and make a
tool from scratch.

00:20:53.090 --> 00:20:54.660
It was just something
I had to build

00:20:54.660 --> 00:20:56.600
in a scrappy way
in my spare time,

00:20:56.600 --> 00:20:58.720
just because I needed to do it.

00:20:58.720 --> 00:21:02.390
And so that's definitely why
it looks the way it does.

00:21:02.390 --> 00:21:06.430
But I mean, in terms
of-- what I think's

00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:08.800
actually really important
