00:34:52.199 --> 00:34:55.810
versus having to flip around
through different tools

00:34:55.810 --> 00:34:58.272
depending on their
strengths and weaknesses.

00:34:58.272 --> 00:34:59.730
PAUL COLTON: I'll
just say, I think

00:34:59.730 --> 00:35:02.280
one challenge that we've tried
to stay, for example, away

00:35:02.280 --> 00:35:06.230
from is anywhere away
from your core product

00:35:06.230 --> 00:35:07.760
becomes a slippery slope.

00:35:07.760 --> 00:35:10.180
In other words, we
were joking last night.

00:35:10.180 --> 00:35:12.367
Next thing after square,
you want a triangle.

00:35:12.367 --> 00:35:14.950
And now you're going to want a
circle, and all of a sudden you

00:35:14.950 --> 00:35:16.062
want Sketch.

00:35:16.062 --> 00:35:18.020
Now on the other hand,
now you want a timeline,

00:35:18.020 --> 00:35:20.580
now you want compositing, and
now you have After Effects.

00:35:20.580 --> 00:35:23.440
Though the problem is
how far do we keep going?

00:35:23.440 --> 00:35:25.330
I think for us, what
we've decided to say

00:35:25.330 --> 00:35:28.640
is, there's a big gap in
the workflow right now.

00:35:28.640 --> 00:35:31.200
Regardless of the tool you
pick for your processes

00:35:31.200 --> 00:35:33.920
of building these
interactions, that's

00:35:33.920 --> 00:35:35.640
the hole we're trying to fill.

00:35:35.640 --> 00:35:37.950
We're trying to say,
you've designed over here,

00:35:37.950 --> 00:35:39.500
and you want to
deliver over there.

00:35:39.500 --> 00:35:40.560
There's a big hole
in the middle.

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:41.810
We're going to fill that hole.

00:35:41.810 --> 00:35:43.932
I think we, at least
speaking for Pixate,

00:35:43.932 --> 00:35:45.390
we have to be
careful we don't keep

00:35:45.390 --> 00:35:47.560
slipping more and more
into, oh, by the way,

00:35:47.560 --> 00:35:50.195
now we're your design tool,
now your pixel editing tool,

00:35:50.195 --> 00:35:51.320
we're your deployment tool.

00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:53.117
You know what I'm saying.

00:35:53.117 --> 00:35:54.700
So there's a give
and take, basically.

00:35:54.700 --> 00:35:56.751
I don't think one
tool can do it all.

00:35:56.751 --> 00:35:59.250
I don't think you want one tool
to do it all, because if so,

00:35:59.250 --> 00:36:01.330
you wouldn't have Sketch.

00:36:01.330 --> 00:36:03.690
CLARK VALBERG: I think
