compositions in production.

00:37:09.389 --> 00:37:11.180
That's something that
we're working toward,

00:37:11.180 --> 00:37:13.190
and it's not that far out.

00:37:13.190 --> 00:37:15.350
So even though it's
very challenging,

00:37:15.350 --> 00:37:17.840
and there's a lot of
logic, some of that,

00:37:17.840 --> 00:37:21.810
unfortunately, is necessary
to cover all the edge cases.

00:37:21.810 --> 00:37:25.290
So there is a very
short-term future

00:37:25.290 --> 00:37:28.290
where you can just do file
export and load it up in Xcode,

00:37:28.290 --> 00:37:31.960
and give it to your engineer, so
there's no lost in translation.

00:37:31.960 --> 00:37:34.260
CLARK VALBERG: I
think generating code

00:37:34.260 --> 00:37:37.190
is very different than
architecting software.

00:37:37.190 --> 00:37:39.680
So even if you have a tool
